{
  "texts": [
    "In few-shot learning scenarios, CRF-based models using BIO tags may not effi-ciently model label dependency due to limited training data in an episode.",
    "From the results, we can notice that CRF-based models have a higher gap between the 10-way-k-shot and 5-way-k-shot than other models.Compared with ProAcT, HCL-TAT model and Meta-Event (1) ProAcT performs 61.10%, 61.18% in 5-way-5-shot and 5-way-10-shot settings, respectively.",
    "But in 10-way settings, the ProAcT performs poorly.",
    "This indicates that in the case of a large number of categories, ProAcT is difficult to cope with Few-shot setting.",
    "Besides, our proposed MPC-CA outperforms ProAcT by 6.17%, 8.96%, 23.59%, and 29.06% in the four few-shot settings, respectively."
  ]
}